sue/41500","fields":{"summary":"DNS doc needs review","status":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/status/1","description":"The issue is open and ready for the assignee to start work on it.","iconUrl":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/images/icons/statuses/open.png","name":"Open","id":"1","statusCategory":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/statuscategory/2","id":2,"key":"new","colorName":"blue-gray","name":"To Do"}},"priority":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/priority/3","iconUrl":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/images/icons/priorities/major.svg","name":"Major","id":"3"},"issuetype":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/issuetype/7","id":"7","description":"A user story. Created by JIRA Software - do not edit or delete.","iconUrl":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=14815&avatarType=issuetype","name":"Story","subtask":false,"avatarId":14815}}}}],"assignee":null,"updated":"2016-06-03T11:21:28.403-0500","status":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/status/1","description":"The issue is open and ready for the assignee to start work on it.","iconUrl":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/images/icons/statuses/open.png","name":"Open","id":"1","statusCategory":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/statuscategory/2","id":2,"key":"new","colorName":"blue-gray","name":"To Do"}},"components":[],"timeoriginalestimate":null,"description":"We just had a query from customer that their software requires a reverse DNS for cloud instances to function correctly.\r\nAnd I had an epiphany that it is not addressed in documentation  :)\r\n\r\nSo  I propose that you add the chapter about reverse DNS to the page\r\nhttp://docs.hpcloud.com/eucalyptus/4.2.1/#shared/setting_up_dns.html\r\n\r\nhere is an example of reverse zone which you could have in bind servers named.conf file\r\nin this case your instances public IP:s would be the C-class 10.2.3.0/24 and your two(2) UFS which holds dns servers would be 10.1.1.5 and 10.1.1.6\r\n{code}\r\nzone \"3.2.10.in-addr.arpa\" IN {\r\n        type forward;\r\n        forward only;\r\n        forwarders { 10.1.1.5;10.1.1.6; };\r\n};\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nAlso since the reverse DNS is convenient to be done in class basis put an hint about that to page \r\nhttp://docs.hpcloud.com/eucalyptus/4.2.1/#install-guide/planning_networking_modes.html  and\r\nhttp://docs.hpcloud.com/eucalyptus/4.2.1/#install-guide/nw_edge.html\r\nfor example.\r\n\r\nI was just cursing that, since we now have few clouds which public ip range is not confined within c-class and now I have to create a zone per IP address to get the reverse lookup going on.\r\n\r\nAnother point, which might not be generally relevant?\r\nâ€“ If you want to do resolve for the internal IP:s and you do not want to address that in http://docs.hpcloud.com/eucalyptus/4.2.1/#install-guide/nw_edge.html \r\n{code}\r\n\"InstanceDnsDomain\": \"eucalyptus.internal\",\r\n{code}\r\nCould be something like this\r\n{code}\r\n\"InstanceDnsDomain\": \"eucalyptus.internal.<yourdomain>.<yourdomain>\",\r\n{code}\r\nThen that zone could be added to bind server with forwarded similar zone as for the public names\r\n","customfield_13000":null,"customfield_13200":null,"customfield_11300":null,"customfield_11500":null,"timetracking":{},"customfield_10005":null,"customfield_10401":null,"customfield_10600":null,"customfield_12900":null,"attachment":[],"aggregatetimeestimate":null,"summary":"'Reverse DNS' topic suggestions","creator":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/user?username=kmeredith","name":"kmeredith","key":"kmeredith","accountId":"557058:ad01e29f-e62e-4f95-b458-a96ea25c65e5","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/8962f6c2075b2cf80ed6daccff85c8a7?s=48&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3FavatarId%3D10100%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","24x24":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/8962f6c2075b2cf80ed6daccff85